'''色诺芬尼'''，也译'''克塞诺芬尼'''（{{lang|en|Xenophanes of [[科洛封|Colophon]]}}，{{IPAc-en|z|ə|ˈ|n|ɒ|f|ə|n|iː|z}}<ref>[http://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/xenophanes "Xenophanes"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/xenophanes |date=20171113060403 }} entry in ''[[柯林斯英语词典|]]''.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://cougar.eb.com/soundc11/bix/bixxen02.wav |title=Sound file |access-date=2020-02-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080216103627/http://cougar.eb.com/soundc11/bix/bixxen02.wav |archive-date=2008-02-16 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，{{lang-grc|[[wikt:Ξενοφάνης|Ξενοφάνης]] ὁ Κολοφώνιος}} {{IPA-el|ksenopʰánɛːs ho kolopʰɔ̌ːnios|}}，约前570 – 前475年）<ref>{{cite IEP |url-id=xenoph |title=Xenophanes}}</ref> 是[[希腊|希腊]]的[[哲學家|哲學家]]、[[神學|神学家]]、[[诗人|诗人]]，以及社会宗教[[評論家|評論家]]。色诺芬尼一生四处周游，25岁生下[[伊奧尼亞|伊奧尼亞]]后的67年继续游遍整个希腊世界。<ref>Charles H. Khan [http://www.oxfordreference.com/views/ENTRY.html?subview=Main&entry=t10.e557 "Xenophanes" ''Who's Who in the Classical World'']. Ed. Simon Hornblower and Tony Spawforth. Oxford University Press, 2000. ''Oxford Reference Online''. Oxford University Press. 12 October 2011.</ref> 有学者说，他短暂地在[[西西里岛|西西里岛]]居住。<ref name="yorku1">[http://oxfordreference.com/views/ENTRY.html?subview=Main&entry=t98.e3330 "Xenophanes of Colophon"] ''The Oxford Dictionary of Philosophy''. Simon Blackburn. Oxford University Press, 2008. ''Oxford Reference Online''. Oxford University Press. 12 October 2011.</ref> 关于他观点的知识来自他留下的残篇，这些残篇都是在后来的古希腊语作品里发现的，因为有人引用了他的作品。单凭这些残篇，他的{{tsl|en|elegiac|哀悼的|}}和[[抑揚格|抑扬格的]]<ref>Early Greek philosophy By Jonathan Barnes Page 40 {{ISBN|0-14-044461-0}}</ref> 诗作，批判和[[讽刺|讽刺]]了许多人的观点，包括[[荷马|荷马]]和[[赫西俄德|赫西俄德]]，还有对拟人之神的[[神系|巴特农]]的批判，对希腊人尊敬[[wikt:athleticism|运动才能]]的批判等等。他是最早的呼吁清晰写作以为后代着想古希腊诗人，创造了“遍布希腊四处的名誉，希腊的歌声不绝，他的名誉不死。”<ref>See {{Citation | surname=Dalby | given=Andrew | title=Rediscovering Homer | publisher=Norton | place=New York, London | year=2006 | ISBN=0-393-05788-7 | url-access=registration | url=https://archive.org/details/rediscoveringhom00dalb }} p. 123.</ref>

==生平==
色诺芬尼出生在[[科洛封|科洛封]]，[[伊奧尼亞|伊奧尼亞]]的一座城邦（现在[[土耳其|土耳其]]西部）。有人说他是Orthomenes的儿子，也有人说是Dexius的。<ref name="dl18">Diogenes Laertius, ix. 18</ref> 据说他的鼎盛年在第六十个[[奧林匹亚周期|奧林匹亚周期]] （前540-537年）。<ref name="dl20">Diogenes Laertius, ix. 20</ref> 残存作品引用了[[泰勒斯|泰勒斯]]、[[埃庇米尼得斯|埃庇米尼得斯]]和[[毕达哥拉斯|毕达哥拉斯]]的话，<ref>Diogenes Laertius, ix. 18, i. 23, 111. viii. 36</ref> 而他自己则获[[赫拉克利特|赫拉克利特]]和[[埃庇卡摩斯|埃庇卡摩斯]]作品提及。<ref>Diogenes Laertius, ix. 1; Aristotle, ''Metaphysics'' [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Aristot.+Met.+4.1010a 4.1010a]</ref>  他的哀歌残篇中，他描述了[[米底王国|米底]][[波希战争|入侵]]的事件，这正是在他活着的时候发生的，这有可能指的是[[哈爾帕格|哈爾帕格]]的远征，对抗[[伊奧尼亞|伊奧尼亞]]的希腊城市（前546/5年）。他从科洛封出逃，去了西西里的爱奥尼亚殖民地，[[墨西拿|墨西拿]]和[[卡塔尼亞|卡塔尼亞]]。<ref name="dl18"/> 有可能他在[[韦利亚|韦利亚]]居住过一段时间（[[福西亚|福西亚]]人在第61个奥林匹克周期发现，前536-533年），因为他写了关于那座殖民地的文字。<ref>Diogenes Laertius, ix. 18, 20; comp. Aristotle, ''Rhetoric'' [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Aristot.+Rh.+2.23.27 2.23.27]</ref> 

根据一篇哀诗，人们普遍说是他92岁时所作，他25岁离开故土，然后又在其他希腊的土地活了67年。<ref name="dl19">Diogenes Laertius, [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.01.0258%3Abook%3D9%3Achapter%3D2 ix. 19]</ref> <ref name="dl19" /><blockquote>在他92岁的时候，我们看到，他仍然过着四处游荡的生活，这与下面的陈述完全不吻合，即说他在爱利亚定居，找到所学校云云。（"In his ninety-second year he was still, we have seen, leading a wandering life, which is hardly consistent with the statement that he settled at Elea and founded a school there, especially if we are to think of him as spending his last days at Hieron's court, It is very remarkable that no ancient writer expressly says he ever was at Elea, and all the evidence we have seems inconsistent with his having settled there at all."）<ref>{{Cite book|title=Early Greek Philosophy|url=https://archive.org/details/earlygreekphilos0000burn_e8u1|last=Burnet|first=John|publisher=A. & C. Black, Ltd.|year=1930|isbn=|location=|pages=[https://archive.org/details/earlygreekphilos0000burn_e8u1/page/115 115]}}</ref></blockquote>

==诗作==
根据[[第欧根尼·拉尔修|第欧根尼·拉尔修]]，色诺芬尼用六音步诗行写的哀诗和抑扬诗，反对[[荷马|荷马]]和[[赫西俄德|赫西俄德]]。<ref name="dl18"/>拉尔修也提到了两篇关于founding of Colophon and Elea的史诗，但是以上这些都仅存标题。<ref name="dl20"/> 没有文献说色诺芬尼写了哲学诗作。<ref>[http://www.classicpersuasion.org/pw/burnet/egp.htm Early Greek Philosophy by John Burnet, 3rd edition (1920)] {{Wayback|url=http://www.classicpersuasion.org/pw/burnet/egp.htm |date=20180108232718 }}: "The oldest reference to a poem Περὶ φύσεως is in the Geneva scholium on ''Iliad'' xxi. 196 (quoting fr. 30), and this goes back to [[马鲁斯的克拉特斯|]]. We must remember that such titles are of later date, and Xenophanes had been given a place among philosophers long before the time of rates. All we can say, therefore, is that the Pergamene librarians gave the title Περὶ φύσεως to some poem of Xenophanes."</ref> [[新柏拉图主义|新柏拉图主义]]哲学家[[西里西亚的辛普利修斯|辛普利修斯]]写道，他从来没有见过关于 the earth stretching infinitely downwards 的韵文(fr. 28)，尽管他有很多的哲学书籍。一些哲学残片可以从荷马的评论家作品里发现，<ref>Three fragments (27, 31, 33) come from the ''Homeric Allegories'', two (30, 32) are from Homeric scholia.</ref> 因此也有可能色诺芬尼的哲学评论可能不经意间在他的讽刺作品里得到表达。<ref name="burnet">{{cite web |url=http://www.classicpersuasion.org/pw/burnet/egp.htm |title=Early Greek Philosophy by John Burnet, 3rd edition (1920) |publisher=Classicpersuasion.org |date= |accessdate=2013-09-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180108232718/http://www.classicpersuasion.org/pw/burnet/egp.htm |archive-date=2018-01-08 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> 这些讽刺作品被之后的写作者叫做 ''{{tsl|en|Silloi||}}''，这个名字有机会可以追溯到色诺芬尼自己，但也有可能是[[斐利亞修斯的第蒙|斐利亞修斯的第蒙]]，所谓“silloi写作者”（前3世纪），把他自己的讽刺作品加在了色诺芬尼头上。<ref name="burnet"/>

